  "question": "Has Boeing reported any materially important ongoing legal battles from FY2022?",
  "answer": "Yes, Boeing reported materially important ongoing legal battles in its FY2022 filing. Specifically:\n\n*   **737 MAX Related Litigation**: Boeing disclosed that multiple legal actions were filed following the Lion Air and Ethiopian Airlines accidents. While some matters were settled (a Deferred Prosecution Agreement and an SEC investigation), the company cannot reasonably estimate a range of loss for *\"any remaining pending lawsuits or other matters related to the accidents and the 737 MAX.\"* [PAGE 113]\n*   **Embraer Arbitration**: Boeing is in an active arbitration dispute with Embraer after terminating agreements to establish joint ventures. Boeing stated it *\"cannot reasonably estimate a range of loss, if any, that may result from the arbitration.\"* [PAGE 113]\n\nBoth matters are discussed as ongoing legal contingencies where a potential loss is reasonably possible but cannot be estimated. [PAGE 113]",
